x4freetext: Two identical detector systems, separated by
10 degrees. Each system consisted of a surface barrier
transmission detector, 200 mu-m thick and 300 mm2 in
area, followed by a lithium drifted silicon veto
detector, 2 mm thick and 400 mm2 in area.
Self-supporting carbon foils made by evaporation of
enriched (90% to 95% 13C) amorphous carbon. Foil
thicknesses were between 10 and 20 mu-g/cm2.

x4freetext: The total cross sections extracted from the angular
distributions and summed over the six contributing
states.
The uncertainties include:
the estimated absolute uncertainty in the
determination of the target thickness and integrated
beam current (taken together),
the usually negligible statistical error,
and an extrapolation uncertainty estimated to be 1/2 of
the unobserved part of the cross section for each case.

x4freetext: For the continuum data, 6Li and 9Be laboratory energy
spectra were extracted from the two-dimensional
mass-energy arrays. The angular distributions were
found to be fairly flat, and roughly symmetric about 90
degrees.
Total cross sections were found by assuming symmetry
about 90 degrees, making extrapolations for the
relatively small solid angle missed after exploiting
this symmetry, and summing contributions over all
outgoing particle energies.
